Responsibilities:
In this role you are responsible for further design, develop and manage a wide range of products and technologies.
Combine your knowledge and expertise with the goals of our business 
to support and maintain a world-class infrastructure and to enable our 
continued growth;
Facilitate technical discussions and decision making in order to 
ensure reliability, continuity, scalability and performance of our 
global systems;
Research, analyze, monitor, configure and maintain the existing systems and identify possibilities for improvement;
Design and develop business-critical systems to meet user needs and respond to/anticipate on technological advancements;
Create advanced scripts to satisfy operational automation use cases where needed;
Install, upgrade, administer and support new systems and new 
functionalities to meet business growth and changing business 
requirements;
Act as an escalation point of contact for the IT Services teams to help resolve more complex issues that arise;
Interface with other departments and work with system users to 
define their needs, identify problems, evaluate potential solutions, and
 demonstrate, install and implement improvements;
Be capable of working pro-actively and independently in carrying out your day-to-day role, with limited need for supervision.

Requirements:Advanced experience with SCCM, emphasis on desktop deployment;
Solid experience in systems architectural design;
Hands-on experience with automation through Powershell or other scripting languages;
At least 5 year hands-on system administration experience on Windows Server 2008/2012/2016;
Knowledge of cloud based solutions such as Microsoft Azure, Amazon Web Services and/or Google Suite;
Good understanding of IT Security principles, including endpoint 
protection (antivirus, mobile encryption, certificates), network and 
server security;
You are customer focused, a team player and should be fluent in the English language both spoken and written.
Knowledge of Agile methodology key aspects and ability to work in an agile context is a plus.
